# Auto commit & push to `main`

After finishing ANY operation that modifies files in this repo, automatically:

1. `git add` the relevant changed files (never `.env` or secrets).
2. `git commit` with a clear, concise message describing the change.
3. `git push` to `origin main`.

This is the production branch; pushing to `main` triggers the Cloudflare Pages
auto-deploy. The user has standing approval for this commit+push workflow, so do
it without asking again each time.

Rules:
- Do this at the end of the task, after the change is verified (e.g. `npm run build` passes when relevant).
- Group the work into one logical commit per task.
- Never force push. Never commit `.env`, keys, or other secrets.
- If `git push` fails (e.g. needs pull/rebase), report it instead of forcing.
